      • wrap

        public static ByteVector wrap(byte[] bytes)
        Wraps the byte array bytes into a byte vector.

        Note that the byte vector will be backed by bytes, so any changes of the contents of bytes will be reflected in the resulting byte vector.

        Parameters:
        bytes - the byte array, must not be null
        Returns:
        a byte vector wrapping bytes
        Throws:
        NullPointerException - if bytes is null
